  <title>
    <phrase>Print</phrase>
  </title>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Printing</primary>
    <secondary>Print command</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <para><!--TODO it: v2.4-->
    Since the 2.4.0 release, <acronym>GIMP</acronym> has its own printing
    module. You can set page and image up. A preview button allows you to
    verify the result before printing.
  </para>
  <figure>
    <title>
      <phrase>The <quote>Print</quote> dialog</phrase>
    </title>
    <mediaobject>
      <imageobject>
        <imagedata fileref="../images/menus/file-print-tab3.png" format="PNG"/>
      </imageobject>
    </mediaobject>
  </figure>
  <note>
    <para>
      See <link linkend="gimp-using-photography-printing">Print your
        photos</link>.
    </para>
  </note>
  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activate Command</phrase>
    </title>
    <para><!--TODO es;it-->
      You can access to this command from the image menubar through
      <menuchoice><guimenu><accel>F</accel>ile</guimenu><guimenuitem>Print</guimenuitem></menuchoice>,
      or by using
      <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>P</keycap></keycombo>.
    </para>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
